HRG Group, Inc. Key Developments

Tourbillon Urges Spectrum Brands To Consider Merger With HRG Group
May 18 17
Tourbillon Capital Partners, LP urges Board of Directors of Spectrum Brands Holdings, Inc. (NYSE:SPB) to consider the interests of unaffiliated shareholders and the Company as a whole in evaluating the unique opportunity to enter into a potential downstream merger with HRG Group, Inc. (NYSE:HRG).


HRG Group, Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended March 31, 2017
May 5 17
HRG Group, Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net investment income were $12.9 million against $16.2 million a year ago. Total Revenue was $1,216.1 million against $1,267.3 million a year ago. The decrease in revenue was primarily due to lower revenues from Consumer Products segment driven by lower sales in lawn and garden control products and repellents due to timing of seasonal inventory sales, reduction in distribution from retail inventory management initiatives and higher demand driven by Zika concerns in the prior period coupled with lower revenues generated by Salus Capital Partners, LLC as a result of the continued wind-down of its operations and run-off of its loan portfolio. Operating income was $143.5 million against $142.5 million a year ago. The increase in operating income was primarily due to lower impairments and loan loss provision expense in corporate and other segment, partially offset by lower operating income from Consumer Products and Insurance segments. Income from continuing operations before income taxes was $53.2 million against $48.1 million a year ago. Net income from continuing operations was $3.0 million against $63.5 million a year ago. Net loss was $51.4 million against income of $15.9 million a year ago. Net loss from continuing operations attributable to controlling interest was $21.3 million against income of $24.5 million a year ago. Net loss attributable to controlling interest was $82.1 million against $24.7 million a year ago. Diluted loss from continuing operations was $0.11 against income of $0.12 a year ago. Diluted loss per share was $0.41 against $0.12 a year ago. The increase in loss was primarily due to higher effective income tax rate during the fiscal 2017 quarter, partially offset by lower interest expense.

For the six months, the company reported net investment income were $23.6 million against $36.5 million a year ago. Total Revenue was $2,405.7 million against $2,476.7 million a year ago. Operating income was $261.2 million against $242.3 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations before income taxes was $80.6 million against $52.0 million a year ago. Net income from continuing operations was $5.0 million against $73.0 million a year ago. Net income was $209.4 million against income of $22.9 million a year ago. Net loss from continuing operations attributable to controlling interest was $46.8 million against income of $2.7 million a year ago. Net income attributable to controlling interest was $130.1 million against loss of $58.6 million a year ago. Diluted loss from continuing operations was $0.23 against income of $0.01 a year ago. Diluted income per share was $0.65 against loss of $0.29 a year ago.


HRG Group, Inc. Announces Management Changes
Mar 22 17
HRG Group, Inc. announced that Omar Asali, President and Chief Executive Officer, has informed the company that he will resign from the company and its subsidiaries and their respective Board of Directors effective as of April 14, 2017. Joseph S. Steinberg, the company's Chairman, will assume the additional position of Chief Executive Officer of the company upon Mr. Asali's departure.


